snippet.title: Suri Cruise Vs Lily-Rose Depp (Johnny Depp's Daughter) Transformation ★ From Baby To 2021
snippet.description:
Suri Cruise Vs Lily-Rose Depp (Johnny Depp's Daughter) Transformation ★ From Baby To 2021
https://youtu.be/fzjJIFEFBME

* Suri Cruise was born on April 18, 2006 in Santa Monica, California
Her parents are Tom Cruise and Katie Holmes.
Has two adopted siblings, Isabella and Connor Cruise, who were adopted by her father, Tom Cruise, before Suri was born.
She was born at St. John's Health Center in Santa Monica, at 3:26 am PST. Weighed 7 lbs. 7 oz. and was 20 inches.
Only biological child of Tom Cruise and Katie Holmes.
She was born on the same day and in the same hospital as Brooke Shields's daughter Grier Henchy. Her father Tom famously feuded with Brooke Shields after she gave birth to her first daughter 3 years earlier.
Cousin of Adem Darmody and Liam Darmody.
Niece of Marian Henry (nee Mapother), Lee Anne De Vette, Cass Mapother, Tamera Jean Holmes (B. 1967), Holly Ann Holmes (B. 1969), Nancy Kay Holmes (B. 1974) and Martin Joseph, Jr. Holmes (B. 1970).
Granddaughter of Thomas Cruise Mapother III (1934-1984), Mary Lee (née Pfeiffer) (1936-2017), Martin Joseph Holmes, Sr. and Kathleen Ann (Craft).

* Lily-Rose Melody Depp (born 27 May 1999)[1] is a French-American actress and model. The daughter of actor Johnny Depp and singer Vanessa Paradis,[2] Depp began her acting career with a small role in Tusk (2014), and went on to star in the period dramas The Dancer (2016), in which she played Isadora Duncan, Planetarium (2016), and The King (2019). Depp has been nominated for two César Awards for Most Promising Actress, for her performances in The Dancer and A Faithful Man (2018). Since 2015, she has been a Chanel brand ambassador.
